	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Videogame Rating Council (VRC) in the Sega Genesis era didn't rate content unlockable only by keypresses or by hacking; hence ABACABB and DULLARD codes in <em>Mortal Kombat</em>. ESRB does; hence the Hot Coffee scandal in <em>Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas</em>. Though we don't plan on seeking a rating by ESRB, I do recognize that the practice of ESRB is the industry's common practice.<br /><br />Would it be too much trouble to offer <em>Action 53</em> and <em>Action 53 (Unrated)</em> SKUs?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

